latestIgtvVideos.caption:
As per Bloomberg, 2 crore women have disappeared from the workforce in the last 5 years and we’re now talking about less than 20% participation of women in workforce. There is nothing that will have a bigger impact on India’s GDP than moving the needle on this one metric. Love the fact that organisations are talking about diversity - what we need next is more support towards working moms, more celebration of these role models and more participation + accountability of men at home. 

The single biggest reason I’ve managed to survive as a working mom so far is the infinite support at home & at work where the struggles & fumbles as a parent and as an employee were not judged! And for women to replace their infinite guilt with pride, we will need more and more companies to give up the judgment, bring out the encouragement, not treat women returning post maternity as second tier employees and of course a lot more flexibility!

@dainikjagrannews and @linkedin  have come together for a powerful #WomenAtWork campaign to make organisations take cognisance of this - and I’m privileged to be a part of something that resonates deeply with me. 

As I share my story,
I look forward to hearing yours too :)

Finally the TEDx IIM Ahmedabad is out (link in bio). Talking about the 3 questions I ask myself everyday:

1) What would I do if I didn’t have to worry about failing? 
2) Am I dreaming big enough? 
3) And most importantly, am I lifting as I’m climbing? 

Here’s the link (it has apparently not uploaded properly on IG) so do check out the link on the TEDx channel here:
https://youtu.be/JgN09GN8ZnY

Thank you @ritvickkapoor for organising this & @shahjiya28 for the slides ❤️

Happy Karvachauth to all the women & men (I know many) fasting. And Belated Happy Dussehra & Shubho Bijoya ♥️

Karvachauth is a 23000 cr business this year as per CAIT. 2.58% of West Bengal GDP comes from Durga Puja related trade as per estimates. 

Festivals fill our hearts with joy and also keep the economic engine buzzing even in the toughest of years. I saw this energy in the market in Meerut, and in Delhi and in Kolkata! And the last pic is the mandatory 12:30am hustle bustle pic from Punjab. India is unstoppable 🇮🇳♥️

latestPosts.caption:
A half marathon race after months followed by another 11kms 🥵 And a lucky podium thanks to a big push in the end with @sham3981 

Running doesn’t help with sarcopenia (3 to 5% muscle loss every decade post 30)! So for almost 1500km of running this year, put in 100+ strength sessions with @_memeansmehul_ @musclefam23 but the ratio of running to resistance training is still not good enough! 

It’s clear to me that post 40 our bodies need strength training the most, but it’s also clear to me that my mind & soul need the running! So, can’t stop, won’t stop 🥹

PC: @sham3981
